data.text: @zakclaxton My folks both had the Moderna vax. One had some slight issues, one not. I had the Pfizer. We’re ALL doing really well now. The only ones not doing great? My dumbass sis & her hubs who haven’t been vaxxed. They’re relying on god’s protection.  Fucking dummies. 😡
@papergrace Nine hours later, still perfectly fine (minor soreness at the injection site as usual, no biggie). Hoping the best for tomorrow.

@zakclaxton I gave vaccinations to thousands of military men & women when I was active duty AF. I was literally an Allergy/Immunology Specialist! If you start feeling funky (in a not so great way), NSAIDS are your friend. Also? Massage that injection site. And congrats!! #VaccinesWork
@zakclaxton Good on ya, I hope it stays awesome. My wife had pretty much no issues, and I was as sick as a dog for a day and a night. We had the J&J.

@zakclaxton I got mine early afternoon and felt fine all day. The next day there was a headache (of course, it's allergy season), possible very mind fever I didn't even bother to check, and shooting pains in the joints where I already have arthritis. Really do-able, and the next day nothing.
